<subSubSection id="BD78F70FF73A0381BD4F3F018433C02E" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="macau records">
<paragraph id="DA20D752EFB2B83EF12A68D975589AD8" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Macau records.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="43A3F64E2E5E893CB63BBC26ED490BCC" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
Taipa, University of East Asia Campus, 28 March &amp; 24 April on wall of Block I building, &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="8B3670E2E0FEFFDDC33E94767EB68040" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pyrestes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pyrestes haematica" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haematica">
<emphasis id="E92A9E91A8DE0776F386E65139DB3A7F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Pyrestes haematica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Pascoe&quot; (
<bibRefCitation id="8A7F40BA4514A9BF27F38087A0492C51" author="Easton, ER" journalOrPublisher="Entomological News" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="30 - 36" refId="B37" refString="Easton, ER, 1992. 1990 Additions to the Annotated List of the Insects of Macau. Entomological News 103 (1): 30 - 36" title="1990 Additions to the Annotated List of the Insects of Macau." volume="103" year="1992">Easton 1992</bibRefCitation>
: 34); Coloane, Cheoc Van, 16 May 2019, perched on coastal vegetation, R Perissinotto &amp; L Clennell (IZCAS); Coloane Heights, 18 Jun 2020, on flowers of 
<taxonomicName id="1544E8461672B7ADF94A693E747DEB47" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rutaceae" genus="Acronychia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Acronychia pedunculata" order="Rutales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="pedunculata">
<emphasis id="2C57C415D79A6AE06C1C3FE44854825A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Acronychia pedunculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in garden, R Perissinotto &amp; L Clennell (MACT, IZCAS); ibidem 3 Jul 2020, on flowers of 
<taxonomicName id="FD2FA0D5C721EF00BB9EE510742C5949" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Elaeocarpaceae" genus="Elaeocarpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Elaeocarpus sylvestris" order="Malvales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="sylvestris">
<emphasis id="1AC6534F5B5D2D864208A74BAD4F78BF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Elaeocarpus sylvestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, R Perissinotto; Coloane, 20 May 2021, Lynette Clennell (https://www.inaturalist.org/observations/79506655).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F3C42ACC376A089C34B862CF9D3B88C3" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="4CF7285537418184CB9968CF0243AE2F" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B61D6C4787B3BE81222E3789B865763" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
In Macau, adults are active only during late spring to early summer and specimens range in total length 10-16 mm and 2-4 mm in maximum width. They feed on a variety of flowers during the hottest part of the day, including 
<taxonomicName id="F0788283A9999BF9C92E7780AEFC4BAA" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rutaceae" genus="Acronychia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Acronychia pedunculata" order="Rutales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="pedunculata">
<emphasis id="8980E5674B4977EE137C5C641E203F3D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Acronychia pedunculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="0F819D58235692BA0A68BF26CDCC447B" authorityName="Prain" authorityYear="1898" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Dalbergia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dalbergia benthamii" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="benthamii">
<emphasis id="E5C2133994AADC2465AC834BCA7516C2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Dalbergia benthamii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="6F88853C2387747DBB13FD0B8F3A4AE1" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Elaeocarpaceae" genus="Elaeocarpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Elaeocarpus sylvestris" order="Malvales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="sylvestris">
<emphasis id="5DD087102DCBBF76FF84FE6A4B637868" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Elaeocarpus sylvestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Known larval food plants include 
<taxonomicName id="5AD32460A96A9B96483C1FC4B22F6AFF" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Lauraceae" genus="Cinnamomum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cinnamomum camphora" order="Magnoliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="camphora">
<emphasis id="2FF50D89FFE1D1E182DA7BD28183F440" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Cinnamomum camphora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="83D73B5AC07CD050FD052FFA46EEBA4D" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Lauraceae" genus="Machilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Machilus" order="Magnoliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EFEDF468F40EA00E3D956CBFEDF55486" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Machilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. and 
<taxonomicName id="DC3A0A7D2600AE4C4219DA232D1B2E30" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fabaceae" genus="Pueraria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pueraria lobata" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="lobata">
<emphasis id="E7C5DD56DC8535ACFE6B6CD755545A1F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Pueraria lobata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="CCF4B41625F3E86D17D56D6FF78503CA" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5656/KSAE.2013.11.1.061" author="Lim, J" journalOrPublisher="Korean Journal of Applied Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="111 - 133" refId="B87" refString="Lim, J, Jung, S-Y, Lim, J-S, Jang, J, Kim, K-M, Lee, Y-M, Lee, B-W, 2014. A Review of Host Plants of Cerambycidae (Coleoptera: Chrysomeloidea) with new Host Records for Fourteen Cerambycids, Including the Asian Longhorn Beetle (Anoplophora glabripennis Motschulsky), in Korea. Korean Journal of Applied Entomology 53 (2): 111 - 133, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5656/KSAE.2013.11.1.061" title="A Review of Host Plants of Cerambycidae (Coleoptera: Chrysomeloidea) with new Host Records for Fourteen Cerambycids, Including the Asian Longhorn Beetle (Anoplophora glabripennis Motschulsky), in Korea." url="https://doi.org/10.5656/KSAE.2013.11.1.061" volume="53" year="2014">Lim et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
